Body: If you ask me, guys, they need to raise money on tokens in order to fund development of that new AirVento TGT technology they are trying to apply. I don't know anything about that dirty oil business (I know much about the technology, though), but I sure do like companies with something substantial, some real product. I'm sick of buy-my-shit-tokens-because-I-think-it-will-change-the-world-&-sector-&-life-on-the-planet-Earth-&-will-for-sure-be-more-expensive-for-a-day ICOs that offer nothing more than a hope for pump&dump. If everything they've presented here is true, and not yet another full-fashioned charade with a copied Phd thesis taken from the Uni library with models and actors playing engineers and downloaded Youtube videos of oil pumps, than this project could be very successful indeed - because it's real. Too much greedy people around these ICOs nowadays, scammers, thieves, BS sellers, that it sure begins to look like a world of banks and Wall Street capitalism itself. I don't think Creators had that in mind when they started the whole blockchain thing. Maybe it's the right time to introduce a serious "Know Your ICO Originator" verification.
